# Interaction Scope and Questions

## Rules

- Do not use multiple-choice questions.
- Ask plain-text questions only, and only when absolutely necessary.
- Do not expand user instructions beyond the explicitly requested scope.
- Do not add extra tasks, files, refactors, or behavioral changes unless the user explicitly asks for them.
- It is forbidden to optimize for "quickly stable" delivery; prioritize exact, instruction-faithful implementation over speed shortcuts.
- If an instruction is ambiguous, ask one short plain-text clarification question before making changes.

## Examples

// ❌ BAD
"Choose one: A/B/C?"
"I also refactored related files for consistency."
"I implemented a faster, quick-stable version instead of the exact requested version."

// ✅ GOOD
"Soll ich nur X umsetzen, oder auch Y?"
"Ich habe nur X umgesetzt, ohne zusätzliche Erweiterungen."
